<p>I'm working on a client for a REST webservice and using Resteasy v3.0 like this:</p>  <pre><code>    ResteasyClient client = new ResteasyClientBuilder().build();     ResteasyWebTarget target = client.target("http://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com");     IPosts postsProxy = target.proxy(IPosts.class);     String jsonPosts = null;     try {         jsonPosts = postsProxy.getPosts();     } catch (ClientResponseFailure ex) {         // process exception     } </code></pre>  <p>The "<strike>ClientResponseFailure</strike>" class is deprecared in version 3.0. And I can't find what I should use instead. The chapter "Client Error Handling" is absent in documentation (<a href="http://docs.jboss.org/resteasy/docs/3.0.12.Final/userguide/html_single/index.html#d4e2147" rel="nofollow">http://docs.jboss.org/resteasy/docs/3.0.12.Final/userguide/html_single/index.html#d4e2147</a>) for  v. 3.0. How do I handle proxy responses in newer versions?</p>